track.name: Early Roman Kings
comments: Bob's voice has always been not of the classic beauty type. I am thinking he is not unhappy with this development - sounds like the old folk and blues masters he admired so much.
good song, shame about the vocals. Time bob just wrote for Jakob and others and stopped singing.
meh, weakest song on the album
of course it sound like mannish boy, it's a blues song.
Sounds like mannish boy, but i like the lyrics
"I aint afraid to make love to a bitch or a hag." Cool. haha

"Fly away little bird."  Makes a lot more sense that way. So many good lines in this one, it's hard to know where to start. 

"They're lecherous and treacherous / Hellbent for leather / Each of 'em bigger / Than all of them put together."  I like that.
